The National Security Advisors of the United States, Israel, Bahrain, and the United Arab Emirates held a meeting to discuss deepening regional integration. They focused on clean energy, emerging technology, regional security, and commercial relations. Jake Sullivan and Tzachi Hanegbi participated from Jerusalem, while Sheikh Nasser bin Hamad Al Khalifa and Sheikh Tahnoun bin Zayed Al Nahyan joined virtually from Abu Dhabi. They discussed progress made since the signing of the Abraham Accords and explored new partnerships, such as I2U2 and the Negev Forum Working Groups. The climate crisis was a major topic, and they commended the UAE for hosting COP-28. They agreed to maintain regular contact to expand participation and coordinate on shared interests and challenges.